    <ThingDef ParentName="HP_AoD_OnSkinBase">
        <defName>GW_SM_FibroVest</defName>
        <label>fibrovest</label>
        <description>A specially-designed vest worn under Power Armor. Its systems interface with the user’s nervous system and link it to the Power Armor’s artificial muscles, allowing them to move the armor as if it was their own body. \n\nIn true Space Marines, this role is typically played by the Black Carapace implant, which looks like a layer of black plastic under the skin. This implant linked the Marine’s nervous system to their Power Armor, allowing them to control it perfectly - additionally, it also linked the user to their vehicles, giving them a greater degree of control. \n\nHowever, the circumstances of the fleet and the Marines means that they have had to improvise. Fibrovests were also worn by Sisters of Battle and some Inquisitors, who use their own versions of Power Armor. Knowing this, the fleet decided to adapt it for use in Space Marine armor.</description>
        <recipeMaker>
            <researchPrerequisite>GW_SM_AstartesFabrication</researchPrerequisite>
        </recipeMaker>
        <graphicData>
            <texPath>Things/OnSkin/FibroLayer/FibroLayer_Male_south</texPath>
        </graphicData>
